@node developer "Developer Info"

@{b}Developer Info @{ub}

  You want to use AMidi.device in your own program? Great! Since I don't
  have the time right now to compile "proper" developer documentation, I
  decided not to include anything here. Instead, you may e-mail me at
  tomjoad@muenster.de and request an example source and the necessary
  include files.

  If you have questions, I'll help you. But trust me, AMidi is very
  easy to use from your programs.

@endnode

@node history "History"

@{b}History@{ub}

  The story so far ...

  1.05 (September 17, 2001)
  - New: installer script updated to allow user to choose the patch path on
         installation when installing at least in advanced mode
  - New: when started from Workbench, PlayMIDI displays an AppIcon which can
         be double-clicked to break off playing
  - New: sections about "PlayMIDI" and an FAQ have been added to the documentation
  - Changed: changed inner workings of the software driver. Should make it
         more stable and future compatible even though no problems were known
  - Fix: the annoying gap shortly before the end of play is gone
  - Fix: it was not possible to select CAMD as the default driver if it was
         the only driver installed
  - Fix: it was impossible to read out the unit names without locking a
         device unit

  1.01 (September 12, 2001)
  "Silently" released to fix some serious issues
  - New: environment variable AMIDI_PATCHPATH holding the directory with
         the GUS patches
  - New: the tool "Simon2Jukebox" is now described in the documentation
  - Fix: preferences program would always display the preferences page of the
         first driver in the list after start, regardless of which driver was set
  - Fix: installer script didn't work in expert mode. Once more guys, you're
         not supposed to install in expert mode

  1.0 (September 10, 2001)
  First public release

@endnode

